Quality of health services and patient-centred health care: concepts and principles. Clinical health promotion, health service standards 2 and 3 of health-promoting hospitals: supporting and informing, empowering patients. Collecting and analyzing feedback from health care users and planning development activities for service improvement in co-operation with a team.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To develop an understanding of the principles and efficiency of patient-centred health care, and to develop the skills, including co-operation skills to evaluate health services patient-centredness and design patient-centred services.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has completed the course: - understands the principles, possibilities, and importance of patient-centred health care and clinical health promotion; - has skills to analyse and critically evaluate health services individually and in cooperation with co-students, following the principles of patient-centredness and clinical health promotion; - is able within a team to design a quality program/development plan for the improvement of health services.
